						<div class="verses">
									<div id="vers178378" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">1</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Here, then, is one who wears chains in the Lordâ€™s service, pleading with you to live as befits men called to such a vocation as yours.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178379" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">2</div>
						<div class="vers-content">You must be always humble, always gentle; patient, too, in bearing with one anotherâ€™s faults, as charity bids;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178380" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">3</div>
						<div class="vers-content">eager to preserve that unity the Spirit gives you, whose bond is peace.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178381" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">4</div>
						<div class="vers-content">You are one body, with a single Spirit; each of you, when he was called, called in the same hope;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178382" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">5</div>
						<div class="vers-content">with the same Lord, the same faith, the same baptism;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178383" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">6</div>
						<div class="vers-content">with the same God, the same Father, all of us, who is above all beings, pervades all things, and lives in all of us.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3231">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178384" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">7</div>
						<div class="vers-content">But each of us has received his own special grace, dealt out to him by Christâ€™s gift.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178385" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">(That is why we are told, He has mounted up on high; he has captured his spoil; he has brought gifts to men.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3232">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178386" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">The words, He has gone up, must mean that he had gone down, first, to the lower regions of earth.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178387" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">10</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And he who so went down is no other than he who has gone up, high above all the heavens, to fill creation with his presence.)<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3233">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178388" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">11</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Some he has appointed to be apostles, others to be prophets, others to be evangelists, or pastors, or teachers.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178389" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">12</div>
						<div class="vers-content">They are to order the lives of the faithful, minister to their needs, build up the frame of Christâ€™s body,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178390" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">13</div>
						<div class="vers-content">until we all realize our common unity through faith in the Son of God, and fuller knowledge of him. So we shall reach perfect manhood, that maturity which is proportioned to the completed growth of Christ;<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3234">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178391" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">14</div>
						<div class="vers-content">we are no longer to be children, no longer to be like storm-tossed sailors, driven before the wind of each new doctrine that human subtlety, human skill in fabricating lies, may propound.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178392" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">15</div>
						<div class="vers-content">We are to follow the truth, in a spirit of charity, and so grow up, in everything, into a due proportion with Christ, who is our head.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3235">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178393" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">16</div>
						<div class="vers-content">On him all the body depends; it is organized and unified by each contact with the source which supplies it; and thus, each limb receiving the active power it needs, it achieves its natural growth, building itself up through charity.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178394" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">17</div>
						<div class="vers-content">This, then, is my message to you; I call upon you in the Lordâ€™s name not to live like the Gentiles, who make vain fancies their rule of life.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178395" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">18</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Their minds are clouded with darkness; the hardness of their hearts breeds in them an ignorance, which estranges them from the divine life;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178396" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">19</div>
						<div class="vers-content">and so, in despair, they have given themselves up to incontinence, to selfish habits of impurity.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3236">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178397" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">20</div>
						<div class="vers-content">This is not the lesson you have learned in making Christ your study,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178398" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">21</div>
						<div class="vers-content">if you have really listened to him. If true knowledge is to be found in Jesus, you will have learned in his school</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178399" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">22</div>
						<div class="vers-content">that you must be quit, now, of the old self whose way of life you remember, the self that wasted its aim on false dreams.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3237">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178400" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">23</div>
						<div class="vers-content">There must be a renewal in the inner life of your minds;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178401" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">24</div>
						<div class="vers-content">you must be clothed in the new self, which is created in Godâ€™s image, justified and sanctified through the truth.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178402" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">25</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Away with falsehood, then; let everyone speak out the truth to his neighbour; membership of the body binds us to one another.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178403" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">26</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Do not let resentment lead you into sin; the sunset must not find you still angry.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3238">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178404" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">27</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Do not give the devil his opportunity.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178405" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">28</div>
						<div class="vers-content">The man who was a thief must be a thief no longer; let him work instead, and earn by his own labour the blessings he will be able to share with those who are in need.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178406" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">29</div>
						<div class="vers-content">No base talk must cross your lips; only what will serve to build up the faith, and bring a grace to those who are listening;<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="3239">âœ»</a></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178407" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">30</div>
						<div class="vers-content">do not distress Godâ€™s holy Spirit, whose seal you bear until the day of your redemption comes.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178408" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">31</div>
						<div class="vers-content">There must be no trace of bitterness among you, of passion, resentment, quarrelling, insulting talk, or spite of any kind;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers178409" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">32</div>
						<div class="vers-content">be kind and tender to one another, each of you generous to all, as God in Christ has been generous to you.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
